text: Turkey Creek is a stream in Boone County in the U.S. state of Missouri. It is a tributary of Bonne Femme Creek. Turkey Creek was named for the wild turkeys along its course. It is one of three large creeks in Three Creeks Conservation Area. ==See also== *List of rivers of Missouri ==References== Category:Rivers of Boone County, Missouri Category:Rivers of Missouri
title: Turkey Creek (Bonne Femme Creek tributary)
